def service_page(slug,title,pk,kw,ctx):
 paras=[f'{title} should start with a real conversation about the building, the load, and what the owner is trying to accomplish. JAG Electric is based in Galena and serves Pittsburg and nearby communities, so this page is written for the homes, rentals, shops, and remodels common across southeast Kansas and the Four State area. The goal is not to sell a mystery repair. The goal is to help a homeowner, landlord, builder, or business owner explain the electrical problem clearly enough that the first call is useful.',f'For {kw}, the most important detail is what changed before the issue appeared. Sometimes a breaker trip starts after a new appliance. Sometimes a remodel opens a wall and reveals old wiring. Sometimes a fixture is blamed when the switch, junction, or circuit is the real issue. Public listings describe JAG Electric as a residential and commercial electrical contractor handling panel upgrades, lighting, outlet repairs, remodel wiring, new construction wiring, computer cable installation, switchboards, connectors, and related electrical services.',f'Local electrical work around Galena, Pittsburg, Frontenac, Girard, Joplin, and nearby towns often involves a mix of older homes, newer additions, rental properties, garages, shops, and small commercial spaces. That mix matters because electrical service is rarely only about one device. A {title.lower()} call may touch the panel, grounding, circuit length, fixture box, switch location, access, and future plans for the room. Good preparation helps the electrician understand whether the owner needs a repair, an upgrade, a remodel rough-in, or a phased plan.',f'A strong estimate conversation should include the property address or town, the age of the home if known, whether the work is residential or commercial, what room or system is affected, and whether the problem is urgent or planned. If a breaker is tripping, note what is running when it trips. If lights flicker, note whether it is one fixture, one room, or the whole house. If the project is part of a remodel, note whether walls are open, cabinets are moving, or new equipment is being added.',f'Photos help when they are useful photos. A clear image of the panel, affected fixture, outlet or switch location, room, and any visible labels can save time during scheduling. This site uses representative electrical photos to make the service pages feel real while staying honest: these images are not claimed as JAG Electric job photos unless the business confirms them later. Verified facts stay separate from representative visuals: Galena base, phone, email, public reputation signals, and listed services.',f'Homeowners shopping for {kw} near Pittsburg or Galena should know what not to assume. A website should not promise a license number it has not verified, a twenty-four-hour emergency guarantee when public hours conflict, a fake same-day result, or a CRM delivery that does not exist. JAG Electric’s estimate-prep tool follows that rule: it organizes call notes and gives the visitor a verified phone and email path.',f'For remodels and additions, electrical planning should happen early enough to avoid rework. A kitchen update can change appliance loads, lighting, outlets, dedicated circuits, and panel capacity. A bathroom remodel can involve GFCI protection, lighting, fans, and switches. A garage or shop project can raise questions about equipment, future tools, and safe access. Even when the service need is narrower, the best result comes from looking at the circuit and not just the visible device.',f'Commercial customers need the same clarity in a different language. A small office, retail space, rental unit, or shop may need lighting changes, added outlets, computer cable support, panel review, or electrical work tied to a tenant improvement. Public BBB information for JAG Electric lists commercial and residential electrical contractor services, including new construction and remodels. This page keeps both homeowner and business language present without making unsupported claims about large industrial projects or emergency dispatch.',f'When calling about {title.lower()}, describe the job in plain English: what is happening, where it is happening, what changed, and what outcome you want. If this is a repair, explain the symptom. If this is an upgrade, explain the future use. If this is remodel wiring, explain the timeline and what other trades are doing. If this is commercial work, explain operating hours and access constraints. That gives the electrician a cleaner path to scheduling and a more useful first visit.',f'The bottom line for {kw} near Galena and Pittsburg is simple: electrical work should be scoped with care before it is sold with slogans. This page is intentionally deeper than a thin service card because local search visitors need substance. They need to know JAG Electric handles the category, understands the local service area, and gives them a practical way to start. Use the estimate-prep tool, call {phone}, or email {email} with photos and a short description.']
 other=''.join(f'<a href="/services/{s[0]}">{s[1]}</a>' for s in services if s[0]!=slug)
 body=hero('Electrical service',title,f'Local {kw} for Galena, Pittsburg, and nearby communities — practical planning for {ctx}.')+f'<section class="photo-feature">{photo(pk,title)}<div><h2>{title} work that starts with a real scope conversation.</h2><p>{paras[0]}</p><p>{paras[1]}</p></div></section><section class="long-copy">'+''.join(f'<p>{p}</p>' for p in paras[2:])+'</section>'+f'<section class="faq-grid"><h2>Questions to answer before calling</h2><div><h3>What changed?</h3><p>New appliances, remodel work, storms, tripping breakers, flickering lights, or added equipment can change scope.</p></div><div><h3>What photos help?</h3><p>Panel, fixture, switch, outlet, room, exterior wall, and visible labels.</p></div><div><h3>What towns are in range?</h3><p>JAG Electric is based in Galena and serves Pittsburg and nearby areas. Call to confirm scheduling.</p></div></section><section class="related"><h2>Related electrical services</h2><div class="mini-links">{other}</div></section>'+cta(title.lower())+'</main>'
